rComments: Good professor.  Classes are mostly interesting.
typical psych course at utm where the material is easy but the course is graded so hard to keep a certain average.
Her tests are very easy but the assignment is very tough. Her lectures are interesting and she keeps you engaged.

She makes lectures interesting and engages the students in discussion which helps with learning the material. However, she refuses to answer questions about the assignment outside of the lectures and won't show us assignment marking schemes so we know what we will be marked on. Tests are easy but she makes the assignment brutal

I took this class in 2011. She is really great, her tests are fair but are marked hard by the TA's. The textbook is just additional info to her lectures and the test is mostly based on lectures. She is very funny, charismatic and enthusiastic and the class is an easy 4.0

A lot of work involved for this course. Many people suggested it to be easy, it is NOT. The TA is never available outside his office hours (which are limited) and marks very strictly. Unfortunately I was disappointed in the Prof. as well.

Lectures were absolutely useless. Her voice level is abruptly loud at the beginning of her sentences and tends to drift off very quietly. Reads word for word, no elaboration, and slides taken directly from the text. Tests and marking were quite easy and she is quite approachable. Overall not bad.
